        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 7:01AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 701 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
northwest of Rudd, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Rudd...                           Cabanal...
Metalton...                       Connor...
Coin...                           Osage...
Pleasant Ridge...                 Urbanette...
Berryville...                     Green Forest...
Denver...                         Rule...
Grandview...                      Blue Eye...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 AM CDT for
northwestern Arkansas.</instruction>
